:37081,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/10\/05\/tarak-salah-kufr\/","url_meta":{"origin":37547,"position":0},"title":"Sahaba on Salat: Abandoning the prayer completely is unbelief","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 5, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Shaqiq reported: The companions of Muhammad, peace and blessings be upon him, did not consider leaving any deed to be unbelief except for the prayer. Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 2622 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Nawawi \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0634\u064e\u0642\u0650\u064a\u0642\u064d \u0627\u0644\u0639\u064f\u0642\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0644\u0650\u064a\u0651\u0650 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0635\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0627\u0628\u064f \u0645\u064f\u062d\u064e\u0645\u0651\u064e\u062f\u064d \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":23760,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/09\/21\/prophet-prays-thaqif-guided\/","url_meta":{"origin":37547,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Dua: The Prophet prays for his enemies to be guided","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 21, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir reported: It was said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, the arrows of the tribe of Thaqif have pierced us, so pray against them!\u201d The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cO Allah, guide the tribe of Thaqif!\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 3942 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":12941,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/03\/18\/for-rakaat-before-after-duhur\/","url_meta":{"origin":37547,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Nawafil: Four raka&#8217;at before, after Dhuhur prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 18, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Umm Habibah reported: The\u00a0Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \"Whoever preserves four cycles of prayer before noon prayer and after it, Allah will forbid him from entering the Hellfire.\" Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 428 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Tirmidhi \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064f\u0645\u0650\u0651 \u062d\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0628\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u062a\u0652 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":26737,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/08\/15\/beware-distraction-during-prayer\/","url_meta":{"origin":37547,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Salat: Beware of ruin by distraction in prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 15, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said to me, \u201cO my son, beware of being distracted in prayer, for distraction in prayer is a cause of ruin.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 589 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to Al-Tirmidhi \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633 \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u0645\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0650\u0643\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":692,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/04\/11\/dua-essence-ibadah\/","url_meta":{"origin":37547,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Dua: Supplication is worship itself, for Allah alone","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 11, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Nu\u2019man ibn Bashir reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cSupplication is worship itself.\u201d Then, the Prophet recited the verse, \u201cYour Lord said: Call upon Me and I will answer you. Verily, those who disdain My worship will enter Hell in humiliation.\u201d (40:60) Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 3247\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":26334,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/05\/13\/dua-complain-to-allah\/","url_meta":{"origin":37547,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Dua: Whoever complains to Allah, relief will come","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 13, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever is afflicted by a pressing need and complains to people, his need will never be satisfied. Whoever is afflicted by a pressing need and complains to Allah, eventually Allah will provide for him, sooner\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/37547","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=37547"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/37547\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=37547"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=37547"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=37547"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}